The following block implements the pull down part of menu referred to above. It has to appear after the block that defines its visible window (that is: cardTwo) because blocks are drawn in the order they appear and you want the pull down menu to float over the underlying window.
The item block below is a template and basically works like a macro. The way the xml parser works: attributes that have no value are searched for in the current registry first and if not found, then searched for in the registry search path. If found, the attributes (and members) of the found attribute are substituted into the block containing the original valueless attribute).
<item height=16 border=off menuItem font=normal align=left/>
<pull="Select something" fill=white border=black fit=text>
    <one="First menu item" item/>
    <two="Second item" item/>
    <three="Last item" item/></pull>
